EPS for Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (SMG) Expected At $2.52; Ariel Investments Has Raised Mosaic Co. (MOS) Stake


					
						July 26, 2017 - By Linda Rogers


Ariel Investments Llc increased Mosaic Co. (MOS) stake by 8.62% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Ariel Investments Llc acquired 17,688 shares as Mosaic Co. (MOS)’s stock declined 29.59%. The Ariel Investments Llc holds 222,885 shares with $6.54M value, up from 205,197 last quarter. Mosaic Co. now has $8.52 billion valuation. It closed at $24.22 lastly. It is down 7.87% since July 26, 2016 and is downtrending. It has underperformed by 24.57% the S&P500.







 Analysts expect Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG) to report $2.52 EPS on August, 2.They anticipate $0.36 EPS change or 16.67% from last quarter’s $2.16 EPS. SMG’s profit would be $151.82 million giving it 9.55 P/E if the $2.52 EPS is correct. After having $2.78 EPS previously, Scotts Miracle-Gro Co’s analysts see -9.35% EPS growth. It closed at $96.27 lastly. It is down 31.99% since July 26, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 15.29% the S&P500.
Ariel Investments Llc decreased Eog Resources Inc. (NYSE:EOG) stake by 88,890 shares to 166,000 valued at $16.78 million in 2016Q4. It also reduced British American Tobacco Plc Adr (NYSEMKT:BTI) stake by 61,989 shares and now owns 9,680 shares. Goldman Sachs Group Inc. (NYSE:GS) was reduced too. 
Since February 10, 2017, it had 4 insider purchases, and 1 insider sale for $758,708 activity. Shares for $493,340 were bought by EBEL GREGORY L on Friday, May 5. Koenig Emery N. bought $97,038 worth of stock or 3,000 shares. $18,933 worth of Mosaic Co (NYSE:MOS) shares were bought by Johnson Denise C. 1,100 Mosaic Co (NYSE:MOS) shares with value of $25,724 were sold by COOPER NANCY E. MACK RICHARD L had bought 7,500 shares worth $175,121.
Investors sentiment decreased to 0.8 in Q4 2016. Its down 0.35, from 1.15 in 2016Q3. It dropped, as 57 investors sold MOS shares while 192 reduced holdings. 58 funds opened positions while 140 raised stakes. 297.50 million shares or 1.30% less from 301.41 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. Alethea Cap Management Ltd Liability Corporation owns 65,819 shares. Amer Natl Registered Inv Advisor Inc holds 0.22% in Mosaic Co (NYSE:MOS) or 16,610 shares. Paloma Management Com reported 0.01% of its portfolio in Mosaic Co (NYSE:MOS). Dynamic Cap Management Ltd owns 20,849 shares or 0.07% of their US portfolio. 2,205 are held by Perkins Coie Trust. Calamos Advisors Ltd, Illinois-based fund reported 75,680 shares. 84,041 are held by Hartford. Carroll accumulated 542 shares. Moreover, Ftb Advisors Incorporated has 0% invested in Mosaic Co (NYSE:MOS) for 1,701 shares. Shapiro Mngmt Ltd Liability Co holds 0% or 4.97M shares. 23 are owned by Community National Bank & Trust Na. Afam Cap has 0.51% invested in Mosaic Co (NYSE:MOS). 24,664 were reported by Nuveen Asset Mgmt Ltd Liability Corp. Arrow Financial Corp has invested 0% in Mosaic Co (NYSE:MOS). Clearbridge Ltd has invested 0.91% of its portfolio in Mosaic Co (NYSE:MOS).
Among 20 analysts covering The Mosaic Company (NYSE:MOS), 3 have Buy rating, 5 Sell and 12 Hold. Therefore 15% are positive. The Mosaic Company had 61 analyst reports since July 22, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The stock has “Underperformer” rating by IBC on Monday, April 4. The rating was downgraded by Vertical Research to “Sell” on Wednesday, August 31. The rating was downgraded by HSBC to “Reduce” on Monday, May 23. The stock of Mosaic Co (NYSE:MOS) earned “Market Perform” rating by Cowen & Co on Monday, December 21. RBC Capital Markets maintained the shares of MOS in report on Wednesday, November 4 with “Outperform” rating. On Thursday, April 14 the stock rating was downgraded by Cowen & Co to “Underperform”. The rating was downgraded by Scotia Capital to “Sector Perform” on Thursday, April 14. The stock has “Buy” rating by CLSA on Wednesday, November 2. Scotia Capital downgraded the shares of MOS in report on Monday, December 12 to “Sector Underperform” rating. The stock has “Hold” rating by RBC Capital Markets on Friday, June 9.
Among 5 analysts covering Scotts Miracle-Gro Company (The) (NYSE:SMG), 3 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 2 Hold. Therefore 60% are positive. Scotts Miracle-Gro Company (The) had 6 analyst reports since March 22, 2016 according to SRatingsIntel. The rating was downgraded by Suntrust Robinson to “Hold” on Wednesday, January 11. The company was downgraded on Wednesday, January 11 by SunTrust. The stock has “Neutral” rating by JP Morgan on Tuesday, March 22. The firm has “Buy” rating by Gabelli given on Thursday, October 20. The stock of Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG) has “Overweight” rating given on Thursday, August 4 by JP Morgan. The firm has “Buy” rating given on Thursday, December 8 by Bank of America.
The Scotts Miracle-Gro Company is a maker and marketer of branded consumer lawn and garden products. The company has market cap of $5.80 billion. The Company’s divisions include Global Consumer. It has a 28.49 P/E ratio. In North America, its brands include Scotts and Turf Builder lawn and grass seed products; Miracle-Gro, Nature’s Care, Scotts, LiquaFeed and Osmocote gardening and landscape products; and Ortho, Roundup, Home Defense and Tomcat branded insect control, weed control and rodent control products.
Investors sentiment increased to 0.93 in 2016 Q4. Its up 0.04, from 0.89 in 2016Q3. It improved, as 20 investors sold Scotts Miracle-Gro Co shares while 118 reduced holdings. 58 funds opened positions while 71 raised stakes. 41.37 million shares or 0.80% less from 41.70 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. First Personal Fincl holds 70 shares. Gamco Inc Et Al holds 0.05% or 90,000 shares. Moreover, Vantage Invest Advsr Limited Liability Corporation has 0.01% invested in Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG) for 310 shares. Liberty Mutual Group Inc Asset Management invested in 0.06% or 18,860 shares. Retirement System Of Alabama has invested 0.03% of its portfolio in Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG). Masters Cap Mgmt Limited Liability Corp has 0.47% invested in Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG). Jane Street Group Limited Liability Company, a New York-based fund reported 13,390 shares. Verition Fund Mgmt Limited Com reported 0.02% stake. Allianz Asset Management Ag reported 54,179 shares stake. 11 are held by Fincl Service Corp. D E Shaw owns 0% invested in Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG) for 5,166 shares. Huntington Financial Bank holds 0.01% or 3,135 shares. Cibc Ww Markets accumulated 0% or 3,452 shares. Acadian Asset Management invested in 96 shares or 0% of the stock. Ameritas Investment Inc has 14,013 shares for 0.07% of their portfolio.








By Linda Rogers
