Analysts See $2.52 EPS for Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (SMG)


					

						July 21, 2017 - By Clifton Ray


Investors sentiment increased to 0.93 in Q4 2016. Its up 0.04, from 0.89 in 2016Q3. It increased, as 20 investors sold Scotts Miracle-Gro Co shares while 118 reduced holdings. 58 funds opened positions while 71 raised stakes. 41.37 million shares or 0.80% less from 41.70 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported.
 Bb&T holds 0.28% or 145,458 shares. Appleton Ptnrs Ma invested in 15,508 shares. Fuller & Thaler Asset Inc stated it has 0% of its portfolio in Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG). 52,516 are owned by Susquehanna Intl Group Inc Llp. Commonwealth Equity Svcs reported 0.01% stake. Us Retail Bank De has invested 0% in Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG). Lord Abbett And Co Ltd Liability Com reported 119,305 shares. Verition Fund Management Limited Liability Co has 0.02% invested in Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG). Da Davidson has 0.02% invested in Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG). Long Road Invest Counsel invested in 0.83% or 11,300 shares. Blackrock Fund Advsrs holds 0.03% in Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG) or 1.77M shares. Metropolitan Life Insurance holds 0.03% in Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG) or 43,230 shares. Envestnet Asset Mngmt has 11,487 shares. Nicholas Prtnrs Lp stated it has 35,364 shares. Century Capital Management Ltd Co invested 0.86% in Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG).

Since February 6, 2017, it had 0 buys, and 9 sales for $6.33 million activity. $2.93M worth of Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG) shares were sold by HAGEDORN JAMES. $893,085 worth of Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG) was sold by Lukemire Michael C. Johnson Stephen L had sold 3,327 shares worth $295,183 on Wednesday, May 3. $332,649 worth of Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG) was sold by Smith Ivan C on Monday, May 1. Another trade for 4,259 shares valued at $381,020 was made by HAGEDORN PAUL on Tuesday, May 9. Shares for $283,588 were sold by HAGEDORN KATHERINE LITTLEFIELD on Monday, February 6.






Analysts await Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG) to report earnings on August, 2. They expect $2.52 earnings per share, up 16.67 % or $0.36 from last year’s $2.16 per share. SMG’s profit will be $148.11 million for 9.33 P/E if the $2.52 EPS becomes a reality. After $2.78 actual earnings per share reported by Scotts Miracle-Gro Co for the previous quarter, Wall Street now forecasts -9.35 % negative EPS growth. About 142,766 shares traded. Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG) has risen 31.99% since July 22, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 15.29% the S&P500.
Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG) Ratings Coverage
Among 5 analysts covering Scotts Miracle-Gro Company (The) (NYSE:SMG), 3 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 2 Hold. Therefore 60% are positive. Scotts Miracle-Gro Company (The) had 6 analyst reports since March 22, 2016 according to SRatingsIntel. As per Thursday, August 4, the company rating was upgraded by JP Morgan. Suntrust Robinson downgraded the stock to “Hold” rating in Wednesday, January 11 report. The stock of Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG) earned “Buy” rating by Gabelli on Thursday, October 20. The stock has “Buy” rating by Bank of America on Thursday, December 8. The stock of Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG) earned “Hold” rating by SunTrust on Wednesday, January 11. The stock has “Neutral” rating by JP Morgan on Tuesday, March 22.
The Scotts Miracle-Gro Company is a maker and marketer of branded consumer lawn and garden products. The company has market cap of $5.53 billion. The Company’s divisions include Global Consumer. It has a 27.66 P/E ratio. In North America, its brands include Scotts and Turf Builder lawn and grass seed products; Miracle-Gro, Nature’s Care, Scotts, LiquaFeed and Osmocote gardening and landscape products; and Ortho, Roundup, Home Defense and Tomcat branded insect control, weed control and rodent control products.
More notable recent Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG) news were published by: Seekingalpha.com which released: “Scotts Miracle-Grow: Set To Benefit From Recreational Pot” on July 03, 2017, also Nasdaq.com with their article: “Scotts Miracle-Gro Company (SMG) Ex-Dividend Date Scheduled for May 24, 2017” published on May 23, 2017, Seekingalpha.com published: “The Scotts Miracle-Gro Company: Riding High On Legal Marijuana” on May 15, 2017. More interesting news about Scotts Miracle-Gro Co (NYSE:SMG) were released by: Fool.com and their article: “Better Know a Marijuana Stock: Scotts Miracle-Gro” published on July 07, 2017 as well as Nasdaq.com‘s news article titled: “Bear Of The Day: Scotts Miracle-Gro (SMG)” with publication date: June 26, 2017.


